tip.text: Beautiful with lots of history dates back to the 14th century. Take the introductory talk of the building. Gives a completely different perspective to the visit!
Cute little French town! Check out Hostellerie Saint Louis for a gastronomic experience in the area.
A place where u can find affordable contemporary design. There's no place like IKEA....
Very disappointing assorted sushi! A respectable Japanese / Korean restaurant will not serve 7 salmon sushi in an assorted sushi dish!
Quirky and chill. Toilets could smell better and to be cleaner though.
A real gem! An extensive and authentic menu, the quality of food and portion size is very good. They also have baby changing facilities which is hard to come by in most restaurants of this size.
Take a stroll through green park to Buckingham Palace. Must better journey than from Victoria.
If you like soft chewy crust... Good selection of pizza which differ from the norm.
Really good Sunday roast portion with generous cup of gravy! Awesome...
Always full of surprises!
Love Jazz Sunday!
Beautiful landmark. A lot of tourists around though. Visit during weekdays if possible.
Good value for money Szechuan dishes in big portion. However expect slow service during weekends and little ambience. Typical no frill cheap and cheerful Chinese restaurant
Pilau rice was very good. The jalfrezi was good but it isn't the jalfrezi I was expecting as it should have tomatoes and green chillies in it and there wasn't. The dal and lamb shank was good.
Grilled watermelon salad- awesome and refreshing!
Love the fish and sweet potato fries!
A good hearty roast pork. Additional trimmings on a separate bowl! And the pork crackling is awesome!
East meets West Chocolate patisserie
I love a good chocolatier!
Views from the meeting room gives you birds eye view of 5th ave
The married fava is a lovely surprise! Give it a try...
Totto spicy ramen
Prawn laksa is delicious
Amazing food dessert hostess ... we held our wedding reception here!
Bread and dips are awesome!
The grilled octopus and the Tamara (fish roe) salad is 'muaks'!
